00:37:23.660 --> 00:37:25.030
than other video formats?

00:37:26.740 --> 00:37:32.870
<v Michelle> It's mostly with, for
the mp4, they are able to be played

00:37:32.870 --> 00:37:35.320
on almost all players.

00:37:35.320 --> 00:37:42.260
Where your QuickTime and Flash,
yes, they still have Flash around,

00:37:42.260 --> 00:37:46.770
Windows media player tend to only
want to be played on those type

00:37:46.770 --> 00:37:48.650
of media players.

00:37:48.650 --> 00:37:58.830
Then also the MP3s, it's just like
your like PHP level WordPress levels

00:37:58.830 --> 00:37:59.400
and stuff.

00:37:59.400 --> 00:38:05.690
It is accessible,
but with the newer MP4s,

00:38:05.690 --> 00:38:09.090
it just makes it a bit better and
code is written just a little bit

00:38:09.090 --> 00:38:10.090
more tighter.

00:38:10.477 --> 00:38:10.907
<v Jay> Okay.

00:38:11.610 --> 00:38:12.700
