00:41:07.610 --> 00:41:10.730
What is your opinion
on background videos?

00:41:10.730 --> 00:41:12.450
Are they very annoying to you?

00:41:12.450 --> 00:41:15.820
Do you see value
in them for others?

00:41:18.742 --> 00:41:23.109
<v Michelle> I can see the
appeal in them, but for the love

00:41:23.110 --> 00:41:29.090
of everything that is good, do not
make the audio play automatically.

00:41:30.140 --> 00:41:33.360
Because how many times,
especially if you've been sitting

00:41:33.360 --> 00:41:38.730
in a quiet room and you go to a
page and it's almost like the clown

00:41:38.730 --> 00:41:44.050
from the Garfield Halloween's
episode, where the clown's like,

00:41:44.050 --> 00:41:49.250
"Hey, kids," and it feels like
that when you go to these videos

00:41:49.250 --> 00:41:51.450
and all of a sudden just,
well, go to the websites

00:41:51.450 --> 00:41:54.380
and it just sounds crazy.

00:41:54.380 --> 00:42:01.700
The little short videos in
the header area can be gray,

00:42:01.700 --> 00:42:08.470
then also a little moving
background for a gift can be nice.

00:42:08.470 --> 00:42:11.990
I just recently looked
at a real estate site

00:42:11.990 --> 00:42:16.580
that had a huge hero section where
behind it, was a drone flying

00:42:16.580 --> 00:42:20.520
through St. Louis,
and it was on a continuous loop.

00:42:21.630 --> 00:42:25.820
It never stopped, and if you paid
a little too much attention to it,

00:42:25.820 --> 00:42:27.660
it kind of made you motion sick.

00:42:30.230 --> 00:42:32.210
<v Jay> That's never
a good feeling.

00:42:33.230 --> 00:42:34.620
Oh, we have another one here.

00:42:34.620 --> 00:42:39.100
If we're making a product demo
video that is-- excuse me,

00:42:39.100 --> 00:42:40.500
let me rephrase that.

00:42:40.500 --> 00:42:44.920
If we're making a product demo
video, is there a specific style

00:42:44.920 --> 00:42:48.590
of demo videos that
you think works better?

00:42:51.102 --> 00:42:57.260
<v Michelle> As long as they're
engaging and the person has interest

00:42:57.260 --> 00:43:04.850
in it, in really just
authentic engagement in it,

00:43:05.890 --> 00:43:11.150
then the demos typically work
better, and it's definitely a talk

00:43:11.150 --> 00:43:15.860
about it, show it,
but make it a quick move through.

00:43:15.860 --> 00:43:19.010
Because sometimes there are
like, let me give you

00:43:19.010 --> 00:43:23.340
these 74 different points that
you're not going to care about

00:43:23.340 --> 00:43:25.180
and then show you how it's going.

00:43:25.180 --> 00:43:30.070
Were it's more kind of like how
we first learn to write papers,

00:43:30.070 --> 00:43:34.020
where you give your intro
blurb, you give the meat,

00:43:34.020 --> 00:43:36.940
and then you give
your auto-blurb to it.

00:43:36.940 --> 00:43:40.150
Sticking with those types
of concepts for even demos,

00:43:40.150 --> 00:43:43.770
where you give your elevator
speech, do the demo,

00:43:43.770 --> 00:43:49.100
answer like a FAQ-type thing at
the end, tends to make it better.

00:43:49.100 --> 00:43:53.420
Whereas a lot of
these cooking videos

00:43:53.420 --> 00:44:00.560
or even just the cooking recipe
pages, where you have like 10 miles

00:44:00.560 --> 00:44:03.180
of fluff and then you
finally get to what you want,

00:44:04.260 --> 00:44:09.350
and the more of getting what you
want tends to make the demos,

00:44:09.350 --> 00:44:11.270
unboxing any of those
types of videos better.

00:44:13.420 --> 00:44:14.790
<v Jay> This is just for me.

00:44:14.790 --> 00:44:18.500
I'm curious, in terms of if
you have any advice in terms of

00:44:18.500 --> 00:44:24.430
how to maybe script out or plan
your video before you actually get

00:44:24.430 --> 00:44:26.290
to hitting record.

00:44:26.290 --> 00:44:31.790
<v Michelle> For that, what I've tend
to have done is just build out almost

00:44:31.790 --> 00:44:39.790
like a script you would do for
doing a play or even making a movie.

00:44:39.790 --> 00:44:43.420
Just do it on a small form
because it might just be you,

00:44:43.420 --> 00:44:47.030
but write out,
especially what you want to say

00:44:47.030 --> 00:44:50.540
and then practice it a bit,
so that you're comfortable

00:44:50.540 --> 00:44:54.860
with the wording of it
and then go into it.

00:44:54.860 --> 00:44:58.290
If you're doing something like
this, you can always have the words

00:44:58.290 --> 00:45:02.480
on the one side and still be quite
engaging and just glancing over

00:45:02.480 --> 00:45:05.620
for reading it.

00:45:05.620 --> 00:45:10.590
Having that all written out, it
makes you not do as many of the uhs

00:45:10.590 --> 00:45:11.460
and ums.

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:15.420
It makes it easier for the
transcribers to pick it up

00:45:15.420 --> 00:45:18.150
and it also makes you look more
confident in what you're saying.

00:45:20.070 --> 00:45:26.500
