00:46:00.300 --> 00:46:05.750
Do you have any recommendations for
those autoplay background videos,

00:46:05.750 --> 00:46:09.280
like maybe how long they should
be if they're going to loop

00:46:09.280 --> 00:46:14.110
or any additional
information for those?

00:46:14.110 --> 00:46:17.550
<v Michelle> Well, depending on
how long that video is would depend

00:46:17.550 --> 00:46:19.230
on how long the loop.

00:46:19.230 --> 00:46:23.020
However, typically,
a person's not going to stay

00:46:23.020 --> 00:46:28.720
on that above-the-fold area more
than about 20 to 30 seconds.

00:46:28.720 --> 00:46:31.780
Really, that should be
as long as it will take

00:46:31.780 --> 00:46:37.140
and even if it is a little
area down below that's not the

00:46:37.140 --> 00:46:43.650
above-the-fold that like say,
you want someone given a thumbs up,

00:46:43.650 --> 00:46:49.200
to trying to get someone talked
into signing up for something.

00:46:50.400 --> 00:46:54.050
Still typically, any given
area, they don't spend more than

00:46:54.050 --> 00:46:55.740
about 20 to 30 seconds on.

00:46:55.740 --> 00:46:58.430
Really,
that's as long as it needs to be.

00:46:58.430 --> 00:47:03.090
Then if you do want it as a
continuous loop for longer,

00:47:03.090 --> 00:47:06.190
you've got to think the
longer that video is,

00:47:06.190 --> 00:47:08.810
the more resources is being
pulled from that site,

00:47:08.810 --> 00:47:13.130
which could make the site slower
and then you have even more issues

00:47:13.130 --> 00:47:15.680
than just it being more accessible.

